ABSTRACT
A mobile device may retrieve service information about a
network prior to associating with the network. Utilizing an
advertisement protocol to transmit service query messages,
a mobile device may receive service query responses from
a network that identify the services available prior to estab-
shing network capability. In other words, the messaging is
prior to the exchange of any authentication parameters
between the device and the network as well prior to the
establishment of a recognized session between the device
and the network.
